  "prompt": "What's the meaning of ISO?",
  "response": "ISO has multiple meanings depending on the context:\n\n1. In photography and camera settings: International Organization for Standardization, referring to the sensitivity of a camera's image sensor to light. A lower ISO (like 100) means less sensitivity, while a higher ISO (like 1600) means more sensitivity.\n\n2. In business and quality management: International Organization for Standardization, a global standard-setting body that provides standardization for various industries and processes (e.g., ISO 9001 for quality management).\n\n3. In file formats: Independent JPEG Group's JPEG file format.\n\n4. In computing: In software and web development, it can refer to an \"International Standards Organization\" disc image file.\n\nThe most common meanings are the first two, related to photography and quality standards.",
